results.name: Inverse Euler transform of A000568.
comment: It appears that a(n) is the number of connected even graphs with n vertices, as defined in the Andersson paper (verified for n <= 10): a graph G is even if, for a given orientation of its edges, all automorphisms of G reverse the orientation of an even number of edges. If this is true, it means that A000568(n) is the number of even graphs (not necessarily connected) with n vertices.
link: Pontus von Brömssen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..76
Pontus Andersson (von Brömssen), On the asymptotic distributions of subgraph counts in a random tournament, Random Structures & Algorithms 13 (1998), 249-260.
